9:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Indies on Dragon Rotations</span><hr size=1> To address a few issues:<br>
1. How can your timezone make a bit of difference on a poll? I am in the US but the polls are not limited to 3 hours during OUR prime time.<br>
2. Abraxxus (SP? and sorry) made a VERY good point and my point almost exactly by stating that an indy pays their ten dollars a month where as to be a guild you need a minimum of $100 a month to keep it alive. If we want to get technical with monies in RL that's where it lies.<br>
3. Indy's DO pick a favorite guild to take with them a guild they know and trust if they want to host do it within some sort of time restraint within the system (I propose 2 indy raids per 2 week cycle) or get on with another Indy.<br>
4. I believe in equality but the weight of ONE person on the server should never outweigh a guild. Also I do not beleive Indy's should not have a right to host a raid if they have the money and want to host it that is all them.<br>
<br>
To the individual that claimed FCFS on something that is on the rotation system: Please do not EVER invite this enchanter on any raids you are on. Stateing you will not follow the way the system works is just as good as breaking it as far as I am concerned. <br>
<br>
Btw, the fallacy I see with this poll is that all those that voted NO would probably also be FOR a limit on indy rotation. So far if you go with majority it's yes they can but honestly the majority is in limited rotation because in the very least those that voted NO would want it limited. IMHO.<br>
<br>
