<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 67%</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  of you thought Indies should be able to hold spots on the rotation, with or without limitations.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 42%</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  of you thought Indies should be treated with the same weight on the rotation list as guilds.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 33%</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  of you did not think Indies should be able to hold spots on the rotation under any circumstances.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 58%</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  of you wanted some change to the rotations list when it came to Indies, either removing them entirely or limiting their access in some way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> About this poll</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This was a public opinion poll on the issue of Indie raiders on Dragon Rotations. This was not an official vote. Regardless of the outcome of the vote, we have planned no action to be taken either way on the current status of the rotations list. <br>
<br>
Again, thank you to those who took the time to vote and make their voices heard.<br>
